{"ts":"2026-07-19T11:59:30.415Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"note_add","patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-19T11:59:30.415Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/notes","value":[{"created_at":"2026-07-19T11:59:30.408Z","author":"maintainer-agent","text":"Implemented: update-many now derives unmatched requested ids (same CSV split as the list ids filter, dedupe, request order) and reports unmatched_ids + unmatched_count on ALL THREE envelopes — dry_run, apply, and the all-skipped no-op result; fields present (possibly empty) whenever --ids was given, absent for filter-based runs. Partial-success apply behavior unchanged. Spec covers mixed valid/missing ids across dry-run/apply/noop, duplicate requested ids, filter-run absence, fully-matched empty array. Manual verify: {\"updated_count\":2,\"unmatched_ids\":[\"pm-zzzz\"],\"unmatched_count\":1}."}]}],"before_hash":"b49145eae796fe9128f67e0c8731604c16c08a37370ed1b9d0e8ba13b46f8aaa","after_hash":"d68955d88d4d556b94c818a29d727941408cc8b00c63912c297e5e5e917af106"}
